title: Drawing, "Landscape with the Grotte de la Nymphe Egérie, Rome", 1670–1700
medium: Black chalk, brush and brown wash on paper
signed: Signed in black ink, lower right: D. Tenier
description: A grassy bank, into which is set a grotto containing a table and stools made of inverted classical capitols. At left, a hut.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "Landscape with the Grotte de la Nymphe Egérie, Rome", 1670–1700.
1670–1700. Black chalk, brush and brown wash on paper. Gift of Hugh Cassel. 1958-143-33.
